productCats.name: American Short Hair
productCats.description: As a working cat, American Shorthairs have a stocky, muscular build. Their muscular legs lend themselves to the American’s agility and endurance. They have a large head and full face, medium-sized ears and large, wide eyes.

productCats.name: Siamese
productCats.description: The Siamese cat (Thai: แมวไทย, Maew Thai; แมวสยาม, Maew Sayam) is one of the first distinctly recognized breeds of Asian cat. Derived from the Wichianmat landrace, one of several varieties of cat native to Thailand.

productCats.name: Russian Blue
productCats.description: The Russian Blue Cat is a cat breed that comes in colors varying from a light shimmering silver to a darker, slate grey. Their short, dense coat, which stands out from the body, has been the hallmark of the Russian breed.

productCats.name: Abyssinian
productCats.description: The Abyssinian is a breed of domestic short-haired cat with a distinctive "ticked" tabby coat, in which individual hairs are banded with different colors. In nomenclature terms, they are also known as simply Abys.

productCats.name: Maine Coon
productCats.description: The Maine Coon is a large domesticated cat breed. It has a distinctive physical appearance and valuable hunting skills. It is one of the oldest natural breeds in North America, specifically native to the US state of Maine.

productCats.name: Persian
productCats.description: The Persian cat is a long-haired breed of cat characterized by its round face and short muzzle. It is also known as the "Persian Longhair". The first documented ancestors of the Persian were imported into Italy from Persia.

productCats.name: British Longhair
productCats.description: British Longhair cats are loyal, loving pets with sweet faces and relaxed attitudes. They combine characteristics of British Shorthairs and Persian cats. They are calm, even-tempered that in most cases are ideal to be kept in home.

productDogs.name: Chihuahua
productDogs.description: The Chihuahua is a balanced, graceful dog of terrier-like demeanor, weighing no more than 6 pounds. The rounded "apple" head is a breed hallmark. The erect ears and full, luminous eyes are acutely expressive.

productDogs.name: German Shepherd
productDogs.description: German Shepherd Dog is  a breed of medium to large-sized working dog, agile, muscular dog of noble character and high intelligence. Loyal, confident, courageous, and steady, the German Shepherd is truly a dog lover's delight.

productDogs.name: Lhasa Apso
productDogs.description: Lhasa Apso is a thousand-year-old breed who served as sentinels at palaces and monasteries isolated high in the Himalayas. Smart, confident, and complex, Lhasas are family comedians but regally aloof with strangers.

productDogs.name: Manchester Terrier
productDogs.description: The Manchester Terrier is named after the English city where it was first bred. Sleek, racy dogs who possess a terrier's ratting instinct and the graceful contours of coursing hounds, Manchesters are spirited, bright, and athletic.

productDogs.name: Golden Retriever
productDogs.description: They are serious workers at hunting and field work, as guides for the blind, and in search-and-rescue, enjoy obedience and other competitive events, and have an endearing love of life when not at work.

productDogs.name: Bassett Hound
productDogs.description: The Basset Hound stands no higher than 14 inches at the shoulder but, with his remarkably heavy bone, powerful little legs, and massive paws, he possesses big-dog strength and stamina. They are friendly and easygoing dog.

productBirds.name: Budgerigar
productBirds.description: Budgies known as parakeets are some of the best pet birds. When properly tamed and cared for, these birds can be extraordinarily friendly and affectionate. On top of being small and fairly low-maintenance, take well to training.

productBirds.name: Cockatiel
productBirds.description: The captivating cockatiel is another great choice for anyone who wants a friendly and affectionate pet bird. Hailing from Australia, these birds make excellent pets when hand-fed as babies and raised in positive environments.

productBirds.name: Cockatoo
productBirds.description: Cockatoo is friendly and affectionate bird. These beautiful birds bond very strongly with their caretakers and prefer to be with them as often as possible. Cockatoos can become depressed if they aren't given enough attention.

productBirds.name: Hyacinth Macaw
productBirds.description: Known as "gentle giants," are the largest of all parrots. And as sociable and friendly birds, they love nothing more than to spend time playing and cuddling with owners.  It can be difficult for most people to provide proper housing.

productBirds.name: Dove
productBirds.description: Dove as a friendly pet bird, but domesticated, hand-fed doves are known to be extremely sweet and gentle. These birds rarely bite, and even people with limited bird experience generally find it easy to train and bond with doves.

productBirds.name: Parrotlet
productBirds.description: Parrotlets are easy to care and known for having personalities much larger than tiny bodies. Those considering parrotlets must have time to play and socialize, as these birds can become a little wild without regular handling.

productBirds.name: Green-Cheeked Conure
productBirds.description: By nature, they are intelligent, playful, and slightly mischievous birds. But they tend to be quieter and more easygoing. They usually don’t learn to talk, but their charming personalities are enough to make them entertaining.

productBirds.name: Hahn’s Macaw
productBirds.description: They are intelligent and playful birds that tend to be gentle when properly socialized and handled. These macaws prefer to spend as much time interacting with their caretakers and might become depressed if they feel ignored.
